                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/563: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-08T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1927—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 8—11:04 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>383. Pursuant to the Department’s suggestion in last paragraph of its 123, April
                    4, 3 p.m.,<note n="18" xml:id="d312fn18">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_101">p. 101</ref>.</note> and
                    consonant with the policy outlined in my 322, April 2, 5 p.m., I have directed
                    that all women and children of the Legation leave China at an early date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
